Product Title: Transparent Flexible Silicon Wig Grip Headband, 2Pcs Wig Bands for Making Wigs, Soft Drop-Shaped Wig Hair Bands Scarf, Elastic Grip Band For Wigs Running Sport Headband (Light Brown+Transparent)
Review Date: 2020/12/12
Store: YMSGIRL
Average Rating: 3.3
Product Details: {'Age Range (Description)': 'Adult', 'Material': 'Silicone', 'Fabric Type': 'Elastic,Silicon', 'Number of Items': '1', 'Brand': 'YMSGIRL', 'Package Dimensions': '4.84 x 3.46 x 1.1 inches; 1.76 Ounces'}
Review Text: I honestly wasn't sure what to think of these wig grips but I am so happy I bought them. I actually got them to review them while I review wigs. Now some of the reviewers complaints were that the wig grips are tight and it is sort of true for me. But most my wigs are glueless ( and they usually are already tight) but it wasn't so bad that I couldn't wear them most of the day. I have an average size head. If you have a very sensitive head, I recommend you wear a wig cap because they can pull a haor are two. I do wear wig caps and the grip hold on the wig and the wig does sit still. Unless the wig is bigger than your head and then the wig might move around. But sometimes I don't wear a wig cap and it is comfortable for me. Now to get to the nitty gritty, these wig grip work better than any velvet wig grip I have every used. It has kept my non lace front and my lace fronts still on my head. They come in a clear a a clear tan color. I love using them alot! Especially with the lace fronts because you cannot see them through the lace and they do not leave "bumps" on the wig. I can pull them to the edge of my head and it is snug but not headache snug to me. Now I dont believe they are for people with big heads but I do suggest trying because you never know.
Review Title: They are better than any wig grip i ever used
Rating: 5.0
--------------------------------------------------

Review Text: It is definitely white but it tangles badly, it Sheds badly, and no matter which way you flip it, you are going to just about every weft on top and in back. The purchasing history reveals a consistent preference for synthetic, wavy wigs, often featuring a glueless design. The individual tends to express disappointment regarding the fit and construction quality, particularly with cap sizes that are frequently deemed too small. While they appreciate aesthetics—such as color and styling—their dissatisfaction with tangling, shedding, and overall durability is notable. The sentiment towards most wigs includes a degree of frustration linked to quality control issues. 

Price sensitivity emerges, as the shopper appears willing to return products not meeting their expectations, implying a demand for value. Their positive experience with wig grips indicates a preference for functional accessories that enhance their overall wig-wearing satisfaction. 

Core preferences synthesize around the need for well-constructed, aesthetically pleasing wigs that fit comfortably, with an inclination towards practicality and effective product functionality, indicating an openness to experimentation amidst a requirement for reliability and quality.

target_interaction.title: Not accurately described but not bad either
target_interaction.text: So I bought this wig from Wigoddess on a wig because the pink I had from another company was worn out. Now that is right for this wig. BUT it is definitely not a DARK PINK color. This is the lightess color of pink I have seen. Bow the roots are good and more natural. I decided to finally wear it and it does fit good except it is long around the ears which is making it difficult to glue the lace around the ears. And I don't want to cut into the wig to fix it. I have been wearing so far for 2 hours and it has barely tangled and only 2 strands of hair has come out and that is without me washing it. The lace is a light tan color and it is fitting my average size head. I have short hair. Now this is a wig that you do not have to glue is you are not clipping it back. My only major problem is that they made it an ironed in middle part which means I have to work on it for a bit to free it up which I don't like because the other pink wigs I have own were free Parting wigs and I very busy so I do not have a lot of time to work on this wig.  Now the hair is pretty full and natural looking so I don't believe the wefts will show when the wind blows which is good. It has good definition on the hair line but you can still pluck more if you need to. I know it should take heat BUT I still suggest the hot water method to straighten or curl it.
